KW  - Bayesian time series
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-2879
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jmcb.12771
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract Modeling nominal interest rates requires to take into account the effective lower bound (ELB). We propose a flexible time-series approach that includes a ?shadow rate??a notional rate identical to the actual nominal rate except when the ELB binds . We apply this approach to a trend-cycle decomposition of interest rates and macro-economic variables that generates competitive interest-rate forecasts. Our estimates of the real-rate trend have edged down somewhat in recent decades, but not significantly so. We identify monetary policy shocks from shadow-rate surprises and find that they were particularly effective at stimulating economic activity during the ELB period.
ER  - 

